rComments: An all-around amazing professor. He gives very detailed examples and clear explanations. He was very accessible outside of class and wants to make sure his students succeed.

One of the best math profs I've ever had. His lectures are detailed and very well explained. Provides lots of homework and past midterms/exams for practice. His tests are nearly identical to the course material covered in class.
Professor Liao was one of the best math teachers I've ever had. He makes the lectures clear, uploads tons of past midterms and exams, and cares about the students. Overall great prof!

His lectures are really theory-based with not enough examples. He is a good prof and genuinely cares about the work he does. He should revamp his notes to be more clear and easier to follow as its hard to go back and understand some of them unlike other profs in the math department. I'd suggest another prof but if u can't its a solid choice.
Nice Guy. Nothing special but nothing bad

Great prof! Explains things well and provides past midterms and finals that are almost identical to the current. Make sure to participate in the DGD's, and study the past exams as well as textbook work and you'll do great in this course. Highly recommend taking his class if you can!

Best prof I had this semester. He tells you the first week of class what to do to succeed in the class and there are never any surprises on midterms/exams. Do the homework, go to DGDs, and redo the old midterms and old exams and there is no way you wont succeed in this class. I did all this and got perfect on the midterms and a 94 on the exam.

Great prof that explains things so clearly!! The midterms were fairly easy. The final was a bit tougher, but he gave us a very fair amount of questions, so we had more time to think. He lists homework questions in a document, do them. Most of his questions are similar, if not, exactly, DGD questions. Really wish he was teaching calc 2!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: Great guy, very underrated sense of humor, very knowledgeable, and will make accommodations for students. Will never go off on a tangent about something random or useless during a lecture. Post notes and suggested exercises from textbook and past midterms.
Literally the only prof that could make me understand calculus

This prof is a amazing. Probably would've failed if it wasn't for him. Does everything in his power to give his students the best possible grade. Always willing to meet to answer questions, and never seen a prof answer emails this quick. As for the class, it is real tough, goodluck, you'll need it.
Might just be me but i dont like how its only 2 midterms and a final. But I really like the way he teaches, hes a very solid prof.

I wish all my profs are like him. He is very clear on everything and would post all resource online for you to review anytime. But do know it's MATH, if you don't study hard, good prof alone doesn't make you pass :s

Best prof ever! As long as you did well in high school math this course should be easy. I think it's enough to attend class and do some homework questions for each section. Attend the DGDs because the midterms and exam questions are similar to the DGD level. MC questions are worth 2 marks each (I think it's like that for other math class as well).
Among all my professors, he is the only one who will not test knowledge that he has not taught, and you can always ask him about mark, he will change it if he thinks you can take the mark.

Very good professor, midterms and exam were challenging but fair. He provided us with past exams. DGD was not mandatory, but without it you are very unlikely to be successful. He cares about his students, holds lots of office hours and is accessible outside of class. Watch the lectures, do the homework and go to the DGDs and you will succeed.
He has office hours very frequently and he has two tests then the finals, his lectures are very good and you gotta earn your grades. He provides older midterms and finals for revision

Professor Liao's notes are clear and organized. He posts his notes after every class which is great if you can't make it to class. I praise his effort for the video lectures during the pandemic, it was straightforward and provides a clear understanding of the subject.

A great professor for a hard class. Speaks clearly and knows lecture plans by heart to deliver effective lectures. Very helpful in office hours and for how to do better in the class. The dude straight advocated for us to get a really tough integral removed from our midterm 1 and the faculty did. MVP
Very lovely professor. Lectures very well.

Awesome and interesting math prof. Provides sample exams which are identical to midterms which is nice. Very smart and knows how to answer all sorts of questions. Very approachable and lectures are very interesting and not boring at all. Would 100% take him again for future courses as he is knowledgeable, EASY, and actually cares for his students.
Provides old midterms and final that are identical to the ones he gives which makes it really easy to do well in his class.

What a great prof! Only downside is he sometimes goes over the theory behind some of the concepts, which in my opinion can make things more confusing sometimes. Be aware that the exam is much more difficult than the midterms. Go over the practice midterms and their answers and you will do fine.

Im just an idiot in math, this prof is your goldmine. Lectures are clear, will stop and ask if anyone needs clarification. Responds to emails and no stupid questions with him. Posts old midterms and EXAM with solutions. Only drawback is Möbius assignments, time consuming and tricky, but theyre chosen by the department not him. GET THIS PROF !
Very good prof

A very caring and smart professor. Explains all lectures really well. A guy with a great sense of humour too!! I would take him again if I could. Really helped my GPA! PS: course is very cumulative, so you need to be comfortable with every lesson

I love him! he wasn't the one who made our exams and midterms, so in his notes he'd always put examples from previous exams which almost always showed up on evaluations. he is sweet, cares about his students, explains things in a simple and concise manner, is extremely organized and posts all his notes. clearly a very smart guy

His questions are so hard. I do not know if he read the previous review and started changing his questions. Now he does not give usquestions from the notes. hegives us random weird questions that he did not teach us how to do and we are supposed to study past midterms. Isn't he supposed to teach us how to do them or are we suppose to look at them.
very confusing

This pro is the easiest math prof at UOttawa. He basically almost gives you the questions that are on the tests and exam in advance. Tests were extremely easy and same as the notes. He posts all of the notes online and he has a lot of office hours. He really wants everybody to get good marks.

Very caring prof. He also understand students pretty well. Always make sure that everyone is following. He also post his lecture notes on bright space. Explain things pretty clear. Personally not a big math person, but I followed just fine. Just spend your time for the lecture and sometimes do your homework you will just be good.
AMAZING PROF! Attend all of his lectures and you'll get an easy A+
